column5: Wow, what a beast Terry, congrats!
At least we know where some of the whitefish went......
Nice greaser terry !!!!! That's a beauty simcoe tank man !!!!! Cheers on your new PB !!!!!
Hold the fish on the inside gill plate when taking a pic, it will come out a lot better  Nice fish man, giant tail on that thing!
yeah we were far more interested in getting it back in the water and revived ,then a good picture..if it died I would have great shots....lol
Ya,we were very carefull to get it out of the net,quick pic and back in. With surface temps at 72 and the themro at around 50 fow,it,s best to burp and quick release.
You could have had some greasy BBQ as well!
nice fish terry congrats
WOW!!!

It was one of those days. Big fish eight off the bat and nothing else to show,but what a great fish. This fish was fat. 15+ easy.  Ride out was nice.    Get there and the graph is loaded.    10 minutes in and Terrys rod pops,and dives down. It was one of those what the hell,Im getting spooled. Then he got the fish under control sorta,before another bolt to the bottom.    Getting closer    Get it in the net and pop out comes the lure. Whew.   Nice fish buddy. Pic does not do this fish justice..
wow it doesn't  look anywhere near what it was..wheres the  photoshop button
What a monster.  Natural?
Tank for sure, gotta love beer bellied lakers!
Beauty! You're really picking them off this season. Must be the lucky boat.
Just look at the size of the tail. HUGE.
just checked my zipper

Beast man!!! Nice laker for sure.... It is always quality or quantity ... Why can't it just be BOTH it seems lol won't complain but which would you guys take? A day of two dozen ok fish or a single PB?
Nice fish.  Really dark for simcoe
Really nice looking fish guys!!!Looked like a decent morning as well.
wow beauty laker for sure...got a trolling rod/reel now with some leadcore...going to try and find one on my camping trip next month, one of those would be unreal!  Thanks for sharing
You need a better photographer... maybe my phone will ring next time you're going out!! LOL
when ever you want  3 weeks of vacation
Been lucky enough to have both great days of many fish,and today was a great day of one great fish. I,ll take them both.
Will see what we find out on Tuesday and maybe we can work something in.... if we're not presented with enough time to get North for a bit.
Very nice congrats terry
Both is a fine answer lol
great job, looks like a beauty
That's a giant Simcoe laker , Nice one !!
That's a tank alright, congrats.
Great fish indeed!!
wow!  What a hog!  Thanx for the pix
Beauty thick bellied fish Terry. Congrats..
Nice laker , good old lady Simcoe is really producing some tank lake trout this year . Congrats
